ACDS Footer

Footers help users find what they need after scrolling to the bottom of a page. They provide supplementary information such as copyright, ABN details, contact information, links to other pages within the website, and email and social media links.

COMPONENT NAME 

  

AcdsFooter 

 


 ANATOMY 


The footer of a website sits at the bottom of every single web page and can sometimes contain links to other content on a website or to external sites. The footer is used to communicate to users when they've reached the bottom of the page. The footer is usually made up of a container, a logo, links and informative text.   



1.   Logo: Placed for visual identity and branding. 

2.   Container: Holds all of the components and elements that make up a footer component. 

3.   Links : Useful in directing users to other areas of the site to learn more about different information. 

4.   Text: Informative text, displaying the contact number, trading hours and the copy right notice. 



USAGE 


There are two ways to use the Footer component: 


  • In Experience cloud, from the Component List, drag and drop the Footer component onto a page layout slot. To make the component appear in every page, drop the component onto a shared slot. Customize the component in the Properties popup. 
  • Include the Footer component in a custom LWC to feed dynamic data into the Footer component. 


The Footer component is design to work closely with the Header and Navigation components to create optimal responsive user experience, they work best when using the ACDS theme layout to arrange the three components together in Experience cloud environment. See more detail on the ACDS theme layout.
